Information We Collect
We may collect the following information from users who interact with the Bot:

Discord user ID
Discord username and discriminator
Messages sent by users to the Bot
Time and date of messages sent by users to the Bot
Other information voluntarily provided by users to the Bot
How We Use Your Information
We may use the information collected from users for the following purposes:

To provide and maintain the Bot's services
To personalize user experience and respond to user inquiries
To improve the Bot's services
To communicate with users about the Bot and related services
To detect and prevent fraud or misuse of the Bot
Information Sharing
We may share users' personal information with third parties under the following circumstances:

With Discord, our hosting platform, to provide the Bot's services
With third-party service providers who assist us in providing and maintaining the Bot's services
To comply with legal obligations or requests from law enforcement agencies
We will not sell or rent users' personal information to third parties.

Information Security
We take appropriate security measures to protect users' personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.

Data Retention
We will retain users' personal information only for as long as necessary to provide the Bot's services and as required by applicable laws and regulations.

Changes to this Policy
We may update this Policy from time to time by posting a new version on our website. Users should check this page periodically to ensure they are familiar with any changes to the Policy.

Contact Information
If you have any questions or concerns about this Policy, please contact Shemly#0001.

By using Mystery Bot, you consent to the collection, use, and sharing of your personal information as described in this Policy. If you do not consent to this Policy, you may not use the Bot.
